<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
Only known from central and southwest 
<normalizedToken originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Querétaro">Queretaro</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Michoacán">Michoacan</normalizedToken>
, State of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
, Guanajuato and Hidalgo). Ascocarps always associated with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Quercus</taxonomicName>
species (
<taxonomicName genus="Q." lsidName="Q. crassifolia" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="crassifolia">Q. crassifolia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Q." lsidName="Q. polymorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="polymorpha">Q. polymorpha</taxonomicName>
). An EcM association with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Quercus</taxonomicName>
has been verified (MH174661) and its DNA has been recovered only from soil in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Quercus</taxonomicName>
forest in Hidalgo, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
